This paper deals with the task of Multimodal Neural Machine Translation (MNMT) which involves generating a translated sentence describing an image given the image and a source description in English. This task involves both computer vision and natural language processing, making it likely to belong to the categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of richer visual features, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the use of word embeddings, which is a common topic in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
